page.title: 14Natural History Walk.(Moor)
page.content:
SLEIGHTS MOOR (21.7.85) The following species were noticed during a 10 minute walk along the wall at the edge of the moor.The list does not include all the species which were present.
Kestrel (Falco tinnunclus) Wood pigeon (Columba palumbus) Swift (Apus apus) Carrion Crow (Corvus corone corone) Meadow Pipit (Anthus pratensis) Reed Bunting (Emberiza pusilla)
Lichen (Cladonia sp) Bog moss (Sphagnum sp) Cotton grass (Eriophorum sp) Tormentil (Potentilla erecta) Bell heather (Erica cinerea) Cross leaved heath (Erica tetralix) Ling (Calluna vulgaris) Bilberry (Vaccinium myrtilus)
